Spider Graphics---------------Spider Graphics is an Ada package for doing simple "turtle graphics"from an Ada program using a text terminal. This distribution containsa package specification spider.ads, the package body spider.adb, anda number of programs showing the various spider operations.A workbook is available which offers a self-paced introductionto programming using the Spider Graphics package.  Contact:	Cindy Decker, Publications Assistant	Textbook Department	El Corral Bookstore 	California Polytechnic State University	San Luis Obispo, CA 93407In addition, a stand-alone simulation called "Spider Draw"which runs under DOS is available from the author. Contact:	Dr. John Dalbey	Computer Science Department	California Polytechnic State University	San Luis Obispo, CA 93407	jdalbey@calpoly.edu